413 crime, if the Juvenile Court has found there is probable cause to believe the juvenile
424 committed a juvenile crime that would be a violation of Title 17‑A, section 201, 202
435 or 203 if the juvenile involved were an adult.
4 If the juvenile had not attained 13 years of age at the time of the alleged violation of
5 Title 17‑A, section 201, 202 or 203, the Juvenile Court may allow public inspection of
6 the juvenile petition pursuant to paragraph C;
7 Sec. 6. 17-A MRSA §202, as amended by PL 1991, c. 377, §8, is repealed.
8 Sec. 7. 22 MRSA §4002, sub-§1-B, ¶B, as enacted by PL 1997, c. 715, Pt. B, §1,
9 is amended by repealing subparagraph (2).
10 Sec. 8. 22 MRSA §4055, sub-§1-A, ¶B, as amended by PL 2015, c. 360, §4, is
11 further amended by repealing subparagraph (2).
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill eliminates the crime of felony murder and removes cross-references to that
1144 crime in the Maine Revised Statutes.
